        "content": "📌 Fetch Yesterday Issues\n\nCalls the PMS (Redmine) API to fetch all issues/tasks that were updated today. Fetches up to 100 tasks at once, sorted by project. Uses an API key in the header for authentication.\n\n\n📌 Split Issues\n\nTakes the bulk list of issues returned by the API and splits them into individual items — one item per issue. Also attaches the today and displayDate values to each so every downstream node knows which date it's working on. If no issues found, returns a \"no activity\" flag.\n\n\n📌 Fetch Issue Detail\n\nFor each individual issue, calls the PMS API again to get the full detail — including journals (comments/history), spent hours, changesets, and watchers. This gives the complete picture of what happened on that task today.\n\n\n📌 Extract Today's Activity\n\nParses the full issue detail and extracts only activity that happened specifically today— filters journals by date, collects comments, status changes, spent time, assignee changes. Builds a clean activity text block per task along with project name, task title, status, and assignee.",
